Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a
#tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, @White Cumin Seeds{1%sachet} and
@salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down
to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pot{} from the heat
(still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until
ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1%unit}, then quarter lengthways.
Chop into @chicken to 2cm chunks{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and courgette to
the pan. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and
> its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the chicken is cooked, lower the heat to medium,

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Ginger Puree{15%g} and @Pasanda Style
Seasoning{1%sachet}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and
@Water for the Sauce{150%ml}. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened,
~{4-5%mins}.

Add the @Creme Fraiche{75%g} to the chicken pan. Stir to combine, bring
to the boil, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share
between your bowls.

Top with the pasanda spiced chicken curry.

Enjoy!